HEADWORD: Bloodstone
<hw>Blood"stone`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Min.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>A green siliceous stone sprinkled with red jasper, as
if with blood; hence the name; -- called also
<altname>heliotrope</altname>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Hematite, an ore
of iron yielding a blood red powder or ⟦ldquo⟧streak.⟦rdquo⟧</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bloodstroke</ent>⟦br⟧
